1600142400.title: Bargain Hunt
1600142400.descr: Bargain Hunt visits the largest antiques fair in Europe – Newark in Nottinghamshire. Christina travels to the Derby Silk Mill to uncovers a tale of espionage, revenge and murder in Britain's first ever factory.

1600145100.title: Bargain Hunt
1600145100.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1600147800.title: Keeping Up Appearances
1600147800.descr: The first episode of Roy Clarke's sitcom about fastidious housewife Hyacinth Bucket and the strain her obsession with etiquette puts on the rest of her family sees Hyacinth's father have a nasty accident with a milk bottle.

1600149600.title: Call the Midwife
1600149600.descr: Period drama series set in East London in the 1950s, following the life and work of a young midwife Jenny Lee and her colleagues at the Nonnatus House nursing convent. They serve the poor society of Poplar, London. Their main duty is to help bring safe birth to women and help them look after their newborns.

1600192800.title: Keeping Up Appearances
1600192800.descr: The story revolves around Hyacinth Bucket, a housewife from a lower class whose only aim in life is to impress others with her etiquette and social skills and climb the social ladder. 1600202100.title: W1A
1600202100.descr: Following on from the BAFTA award-winning Twenty Twelve: the BBC has a new Head of Values, Ian Fletcher and he's been given the huge task of sorting the corporation out, he has to "restructure" it. The BBC is becoming under a huge load of pressure with the content that they produce. This British comedy is the BBC realising where it goes wrong and is essentially criticising itself.

1600203900.title: Our Girl
1600203900.descr: Set in the time of Britain's withdrawal from Afghanistan, Our Girl follows the journeys of female medics. It all began when teenage girl Molly found herself in the army's recruitment office, after being sick in the doorway having celebrated her eighteenth birthday. Since then, there has been incredible displays of love, laughs, and loss.
